Instruction: Use an approved 'inspect_connections' style operation to carefully inspect all fast-connection terminals between every adjacent pair of modules (PSU–CM1, CM1–CM2, …, CM8–Load). Verify for each interface that exactly one conductor from the upstream module’s positive output is mated to one conductor of the downstream module’s input pair, and the other conductor from the upstream negative output is mated to the remaining conductor of the downstream pair—i.e., confirm that there is a straight-through pair and not a cross-connection between the two lines. Note and report any interface where the two conductors appear swapped relative to the internal polarity marking of either module.
