2026-04-16 12:28:32 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 6 control‑path series conductor (line ‘n’ on Control Input Cable (+) 6)'] hypothesis_explanation='The inspection report states that all module‑to‑module cable interfaces have correct straight‑through polarity and no inversions, but there is a single discontinuity: Control Input Cable (+) 6 has its “n” terminal disconnected/floating instead of being paired through. This implies the series conductor that should carry the supply through control module 6 is open. With all switches ON, any open in this series chain will prevent current from reaching the load module, so the lamp cannot light. The missing or miswired indicator LEDs are irrelevant to series continuity and have been ruled out already by a failed repair attempt. Therefore, the root cause is an open circuit in the series path at control module 6, specifically the conductor associated with the “n” terminal of its positive input cable. Repairing/reconnecting this conductor should restore continuity to the load and allow the lamp to operate when power is applied and switches are closed.'
